{
  "texts": [
    "The paper Liu et al. (2016) proposes a method called Deep Rehabilitation Gait Learning (DRGL) for modeling the knee joints of lower-limb exoskeletons.",
    "The method leverages Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM) to learn the inherent spatial-temporal correlations of gait features.",
    "With DRGL, abnormal knee joint trajectories can be predicted and corrected based on the wearer's other joints, without requiring complex kinematic and dynamic models for the human body and exoskeleton.",
    "The main advantage of DRGL is that the new recovery gait pattern is not only in accordance with the healthy walking gait but also includes the wearer's own gait profile.",
    "To prove the effectiveness of DRGL, the authors obtained a new recovery gait from DRGL based on \"pathological gait, \" which was obtained by having a healthy subject imitate knee injury."
  ]
}